{
  "stem": "10699.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they went up and raided it, that reserve there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But what they didn't know was that it was very bad for you to drink condensed milk and rich food.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they made themselves ill, you see?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So when I saw him, he was all puffed up around, grey and green, the colorings, you see, very bad colorings.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he had been-- he came home through Odessa.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were sent from Auschwitz to Odessa, and from Odessa they came home to Marseilles.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he was the first one to come home to Saint-Etienne.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had made-- had said, if any of us survived, we should come back to Saint-Etienne from where we were the last address.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not to go to Rouen, you know, there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he was the first one to come back, and didn't find anybody.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Eventually, he tried to find out if my brother David survived.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he found out that he was liberated by the Americans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was in Paris, very ill, and in the good hands of the American at L'Hotel Lutetia, which was turned into a hospital.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So he was getting better, also, but fed spoonful at the time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Eventually, we stayed there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were quite a few-- a plane full I suppose-- not airplane, it wasn't planes like today.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a small plane.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It must have been 30 to 40 girls coming home, some in stretchers, you know, in hammocks.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] now, everybody was searching, look-- asking questions.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Even at that stage, knowing what we had-- and knowing and having seen what we saw, we still lived and hoped.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We didn't give up hope, against all odds.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we-- we-- we met up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My brother thought I looked terrible, you know, because no hair, very thin, and so on, but I was just about alive.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So, after a fortnight in quarantine, something had to be done.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Here we were, alone, with nothing, not even a pair of-- no clothing to put on our backs, nothing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What are we going to do?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the American joint at the time, I think, came in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were provided with some kind of clothing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were taken for convalescence to Chambon-sur-Lignon, which, at the time when I was taken, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and still there's no-- and still ignorant that 60 kilometers away from Saint-Etienne, 5,000 Jews were hidden by the Huguenots in Chambon-sur-Lignon.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't know it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't know it after the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Only the last few years, I know it. 5,000 Jewish people were saved there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because the people I knew didn't know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because they would have been there, you know?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The one in Saint-Etienne.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They didn't know either.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So for three months, we were convalescing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the doctors said that, for four years, we shouldn't marry, or have children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why was that?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because you were not in a physical state.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had-- we had a monitor, who took us for walks, and hikes.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were taught how to dance, and how to-- get into a bit of life again into us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then, after three months, we were still nowhere.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We are now with my two brothers, and Janine.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The others came from other cities, you know, some of the other girls, so they went to the other cities.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we remained in Saint-Etienne.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she was taken in Raguhn, so she stayed with us already, you see?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She liked my brother, so she-- she remained with us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She had a large family, but she still remained with us, then, in Le Chambon.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "After that, she went to her family in Strasbourg.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That family, judges, and doctors, and so on, and very religious, didn't suit her at all, that very religious.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She had thrown the almighty over.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She didn't want to have anything to do any more with religion.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She was against God.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There was no God.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that's it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And with me, I come in here, I come in very late with it, I felt, from the very beginning, that death was on our doorstep.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I said, really and truly, were we all meant to die.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I kept believing, because I needed something more than just fight for my life.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I needed to believe that it can't be that everybody will die.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I needed something to hold on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So I was-- I remained a kind of believer, a believer in God.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Perhaps not in everything else, a believer in God.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I think, in my case, it helped me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "In her case, it was the opposite.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "That what she saw, she didn't-- there is no God.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "If this can happen, there is no God.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
